 <p><CENTER>
<img src = "http://www.magetower.com/pics/gunthersig.jpg"></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uajilon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ajilon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/02 10:51:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17942.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric epic</span><hr size=1> Well, being as Aj is my new main and I have an Epic cleric I've left behind on another server I was looking at this thread and thinking some things got overlooked.<br>
<br>
For instance, the Cleric Epic itself is a badly designed quest from the beginning.  If you look at the Monk epic for example, whats the monk doing in the Epic?  He's being a monk, duh!  he's pulling mobs, he has to split mobs, he has to wait for a powerful mob and pull it to his friends, they whack him and voila ... bubbles! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Ok, it's not quite that simple, but if you look at Monk epic from start to finish it's REALLY well designed and the entire quest seems to make sense, and in fact the monks are beginning on their Epic journey from the orc pawn they kill to earn their newbie headband.  Thats what should have been put in on all the classes.<br>
<br>
Whats a Cleric do for his epic?  Duo's with a druid in the underwater tower, solo's the Sol A goblin, the Ragefire battle itself is usually over so fast (now) that maybe one CHeal might go off, pretty uncommon to see RF live long enough for the MT to need 2 cheals, Ixiblat is really the same as RF only easier.  And King note... one fight in the entire epic that acutally required (note past tense) the Cleric to be a Cleric and heal people in an intense fight.  Now people can get ally faction though and coh all the way to royals or even possibly pull Royals out to a much safer area. <br>
<br>
<br>
As to the spawn, yes the spawn was a little wonky after they moved RF to SF from Sol B.  It wasnt going as intended and they had to play with it a bit, they admitted this at Fan Faire and kept at it until they had him spawning where they wanted him in regards to frequency.  Something people are forgetting though is that on many servers Sol B can be a twitchy zone, and when Rage was there, a server pop or zone pop (which for some reason about a year ago, Sol B was going down all the time it seemed) meant that Naggy had to be killed again and then the timer would start all over on RF.  So you could theoretically get 3 epics in a week, you could also go a week and half with no epics because of a buggy zone and the fact that you had to wait for a newbie guild or alts to kill Nagafen.<br>
<br>
Ragefire is triggered, Verant has always maintained that.  Problem is they consider the Vendor to be the trigger and once you hand him pearl you have therefore &quot;triggered&quot; the Ragefire encounter.  Symantics.  RF the dragon spawn may be triggered but RF the human vendor is still a meaningless timesink camp that could be triggered ala the little dorf in Hidden Oasis for Druid epic.  <br>
<br>
I agree with previous posters that the mark of the epics should be your part in the community (your guild) and your friends desire to come together to help you.  Ragefire should not be any harder than Wizard, Druid, Monk, or Rogue quests.  You think that clickstick is powerful because guilds can Zerg rush a mob? thats something Verant can deal with by tuning a mob so Zerg tactics dont work on him, (read Sontalak, not that they need to go to that extreme, but they have the ability to change mobs to make them stronger against zergling rushes) <br>
<br>
There are other issues with the Cleric epic as well but I feel that mainly Verant doesnt need to be quite so restrictive on the flow of click sticks.  L60 clerics leave the game too, maybe even more often than other classes because of the frustration with what can be a very stressful and unrewarding job.  Clerics are there to let everyone else have fun.  While everyone else is busy nuking, piercing, and slashing away having a blast, clerics are staring at a wall or trying to stay awake through the monotony and hit macro button #3 for cheal chain and praying lag doesnt make them late and they get blamed for a loss in a big fight.<br>
<br>
The original intent of this thread is valid, although the spawn timer issue has been addressed Cleric epic still boils down to a few meaningless camps and then one that has a history of causing nothing but trouble and strife.  You can argue that it's the players that create the trouble and strife but that doesnt do anything to address the situation that the PnP, the failure of GM's and Guides to take action when mobs are KS'd, the tactic of snare kiting vs first in force, and one long bottleneck after an otherwise easy path of progression through this epic have created the envioronment that griefers take advantage of.  Servers with lists that act with a sense of community have Clerics standing in line for a YEAR to get their RF battel.  Thats amazing.  <br>
<br>
I think there should be a second Ragefire in VP that is triggered with hailing him or handing in the pearl to a static NPC vendor, meaning actually triggered for real this time.  This VP version would allow upper teir guilds that have no trouble doing VP to go in and whack him, get their cleric epic done and get out.  It also validates the reason to get a VP key, puts guilds back in an under utilized zone, and gets some loots out to people that often go overlooked because melee's tend to not want to go to VP because they can get better loot faster from vastly easier mobs.  This alternative would solve a lot of problems for Verant in a way I think they would find acceptable.<br>
<br>
Sorry for being so long winded on this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
