<br>
That is what the Ragefire camp is, a KS contest<br>
<br>
On Povar attempts have been made to support a list for some time now.  The problem is, guilds that don't have problems taking the camp in force have no desire to consider any such formalities and just show up for the kill.<br>
<br>
My guild's cleric has been on that list for months.  He started camping Ragefire two spawns before his turn to ensure his position on the list.  I am not in a super powerful NToV capable guild, but we do have three Mana Burners and amassed a large turnout when Ragefire spawned.<br>
<br>
Sadly, a much larger guild was interested in the spawn and showed up with THEIR Mana Burners as well.  Even though I landed my largest non crit mana Burn to date (9400+ dmg) we didn't get the kill and so all of our cleric's time was wasted.<br>
<br>
This would have been my guild's first cleric epic.  The other guild has several.  Explain to me how the design for this quest is maintaining some sort of balance?  I fail to see it.<br>
<br>
/gesture to all of you that just say &quot;oh well, your guild is the weaker one and therefore you don't deserve the cleric epic because it is so wonderful it needs to be rare, blah blah blah&quot; that is an attitude that stems from your ability to KS anything that moves and/or your apathy towards the situation because your guild already has at least one cleric that managed to complete the quest.<br>
<br>
Verant needs to decrease respawn times if it wants to maintain a loyal high end customer base.  Period.<br>
<br>
God I am glad I don't play a cleric. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uikeya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ikeya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Ikeya != Chick</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/28/02 9:29:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17942.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: enough is enough</span><hr size=1> This is why I say the cleric epic should just spawn on their cursor when they ding 56.<br>
